---
description: Simple, surgical, assumption-aware, verifiable coding behavior
alwaysApply: true
---

Before coding, inspect existing patterns and define success evidence. Use the simplest implementation that satisfies the active plan. Make surgical changes and avoid speculative abstractions or unrelated refactors.

Do not stop for minor reversible ambiguity: choose the safest reasonable assumption, record it, and continue. Ask only for the strict blockers and consequential decisions defined in `/AGENTS.md`.

Loop until the strongest available tests, type checks, lint, build, migration, runtime, and direct inspections pass or the exact limitation is recorded.
